I have a lot of fun commuting in my ultra-clean '79 Westy... And I'm a
non-pothead advertising professional with short hair ! I *will* admit
there's a Yonder Mountain Stringband sticker on the back window, and
that I go to a lot of music festivals, but we also use the bus as a
semi-daily-driver family car, even though we have a new-ish Audi and
an older BMW as well. In fact, I'm in the process of selling my
perfectly reliable (and air-conditioned!) '97 Chevy pickup because I
just don't use it anymore. But yeah, I do get lots of comments from my
coworkers about being a damn dirty hippie.

The bus is resting in the driveway this week, as it's been up around
100: the last few days and the BMW still has working a/c. I know, I'm
weak... and so very ashamed...

